I went there trying to help a local business. The man at the register was cordial and helpful, detailing the menu options while openly describing a brief background of the business. I give 2 stars because I believe costumer service is key for any business to succeed. However, I regret going there because the Cheese Burger Deluxe was a kick in the abdomen. I felt ill after eating the apple size burger that was overwhelmingly surrounded with fries and almost threw up. I rarely give a bad review and it might just be that my stomach sometimes doesn’t agree with fast food, but I think this feedback could help improve the business’ quality.
